Phylogenetic PCA for morphological traits

S. Robin

jan 2022

Data

\(n = 18\) lizard species, \(p = 8\) morphological traits, a phylogenetic tree \(T\).

  • $ Y_{ij} =$ value of trait \(j\) for species \(i\).
  • $ _{ij} = $ scaled trait \(j\) for species \(i\).
Traits :
  • mean.L (mean length (mm)),
  • matur.L (length at maturity (mm)),
  • max.L (maximum length (mm)),
  • hatch.L (hatchling length (mm) = lclosion),
  • hatch.m (hatchling mass (g)),
  • clutch.S (clutch size = porte),
  • age.mat (age at maturity (number of months of activity)),
  • clutch.F (clutch frequency)
